    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-tofu-and-brown-rice-bowl-with-smashed-cucumber/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>tofu </strong>and tear it<strong> </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-tofu-and-brown-rice-bowl-with-smashed-cucumber/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>torn tofu </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your<strong> miso</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in a bowl with your <strong>umami seasoning</strong> and <strong>cornflour</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until all the tofu is coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-tofu-and-brown-rice-bowl-with-smashed-cucumber/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated tofu </strong>to the pan, reserve the bowl and cook for 10-12 min or until golden \u2013 this is your <strong>umami tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-tofu-and-brown-rice-bowl-with-smashed-cucumber/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the tofu is cooking, combine your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix </strong>with your<strong> mayo </strong>and<strong> half </strong>your<strong> rice vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add a small pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-tofu-and-brown-rice-bowl-with-smashed-cucumber/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and chop it into bite-sized pieces \u2013 this is your <strong>smashed cucumber</strong></p><p>Tip: Bash the cucumber in its bag to avoid mess. By bruising the cucumber, the water is drawn out more easily!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-tofu-and-brown-rice-bowl-with-smashed-cucumber/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved bowl clean</p><p>Combine your <strong>peanut butter </strong>with your<strong> remaining miso </strong>and<strong> remaining rice vinegar </strong>in<strong> </strong>a bowl until smooth</p><p>Add the <strong>smashed cucumber</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sweet-chilli-tofu-and-brown-rice-bowl-with-smashed-cucumber/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cooked rice</strong> in a bowl and layer over the <strong>peanutty smashed cucumber</strong>, <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>slaw </strong>and <strong>umami tofu</strong></p><p>Drizzle your <strong>red chilli relish </strong>over the tofu \u2013 this is your <strong>sticky sweet chilli tofu & brown rice bowl with smashed cucumber</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
